    <stitle>3300 HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - REMOVE - Headlight Assemblies</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Headlight Assemblies</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove the headlight assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0901037">Figure 39, Item 7</hotlnk>) refer to the procedure for removing the grille and
                shroud. The grille and shroud must be removed prior to removing the headlight assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0901036" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901036.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 38. Headlight Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. DIRECTIONAL BULB</callout1>
                <callout1>2. CROSS-VIEW MIRROR BASE</callout1>
                <callout1>3. FENDER / HOOD</callout1>
                <callout1>4. HEADLIGHT</callout1>
                <callout1>5. GRILLE</callout1>
                <callout1>6. VALANCE ATTACHMENT BOLTS</callout1>
                <callout1>7. HEADLIGHT ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>8. BUMPER</callout1>
                <callout1>9. VALANCE PANEL</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tilt the hood assembly forward and disconnect the headlight harness (
                <hotlnk document="s09010_21.xml" xrefid="f0901024">Figure 22, Item 1</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0901037" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901037.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 39. Headlight Assembly Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. HEADLIGHT AND DIRECTIONAL ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>2. HEADLIGHT MOUNTING BOLT</callout1>
                <callout1>3. FENDER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f0901038" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901038.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                     scalefitheight="352px"/>
            <caption>Figure 40. Headlight Assembly Remove</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. VALANCE MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                <callout1>2. HEADLIGHT ASSEMBLY MOUNTING SCREW AND NUT</callout1>
                <callout1>3. LOWER VALANCE / HEADLIGHT HOUSING ATTACHMENT BOLTS AND SLIPS</callout1>
                <callout1>4. HEADLIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
                <callout1>5. LOWER FENDER/VALANCE ASSEMBLY</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the three (3) headlight assembly mounting nuts from the headlight assembly
                mounting studs (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0901038">Figure 40, Item 2</hotlnk>) on the rear of the headlight housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With hood tilted, loosen and remove the headlight assembly mounting bolt (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0901037">Figure 39, Item 2</hotlnk>) from the fender assembly mounting hole.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove headlight assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove the opposite side headlight assembly follow the procedures as listed above.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <para>Headlight adjustment is addressed in
                <emph type="bold">ADJUSTMENTS</emph>
                section.
            </para>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
